being tracked for a while.

264
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:28,524
This is a stolen car that has been
in the office parking lot for ages.

265
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:36,448
These are a copy of the things
Han-mo tried to report to the Blue House.

266
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:45,707
Stop the car. I'll go by myself from here.

267
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:51,880
If you're away for too long,
you might get suspected too.

268
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:08,021
Promise me

269
00:19:08,105 --> 00:19:09,565
even if things go wrong,

270
00:19:09,648 --> 00:19:11,650
you won't mention my name
during the interrogation.

271
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:16,071
What?

272
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:19,825
I can't trust you.

273
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:24,163
Oh, well. Na-Gyeong.

274
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:26,540
You might as well just make this work.

275
00:19:27,499 --> 00:19:28,584
You must make this work.

276
00:19:29,334 --> 00:19:31,879
Don't get caught and don't get hurt.

277
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:37,551
Be careful. Please.

278
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:47,019
Ji-won.

279
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,064
Thanks.

280
00:20:06,288 --> 00:20:07,706
Mr. Oh.

281
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:11,418
You defeated the North Korean army
seven years ago

282
00:20:12,252 --> 00:20:15,214
at the Battle of Baengnyeong, right?

283
00:20:15,964 --> 00:20:18,800
That was the first battle we won
ever since the Korean War.

284
00:20:19,468 --> 00:20:20,302
Am I right?

285
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:24,890
We did defeat the North Korean army,

286
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:29,228
but we didn't win
the Battle of Baengnyeong.

287
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:36,485
Fourteen members of my troupe

288
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:40,906
lost their precious lives.

289
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,452
As the commander of the battle,

290
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:50,457
I think about my responsibility...

291
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:55,295
for the defeat every single day.

292
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:04,596
Agent Han?

293
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:10,018
You wanted me to call you once
I was certain about the bomber.

294
00:21:11,311 --> 00:21:12,437
Assemblyman Oh

295
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:15,023
must not become
the Minister of National Defense.

296
00:21:17,484 --> 00:21:20,445
Are you saying he's unqualified somehow?

297
00:21:22,489 --> 00:21:25,575
Is this related to the blueprint
of the National Assembly building?

298
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:27,911
We'll talk about the details in person.

299
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,415
I'm on my way to the hearing.

300
00:21:39,172 --> 00:21:40,048
Mr. Oh.

301
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:42,843
-Here's the next question.
-Sir.

302
00:21:46,013 --> 00:21:48,348
May I suggest we take a short break?

303
00:21:50,434 --> 00:21:53,520
Before we confirm the hearing report
about Mr. Oh,

304
00:21:53,603 --> 00:21:56,648
there's something I'd like to discuss
with our party members.

305
00:21:58,942 --> 00:21:59,901
Please, sir.

306
00:22:02,612 --> 00:22:05,490
As Ms. Yun suggested,
we'll take a short break.

307
00:23:02,255 --> 00:23:03,507
It's getting too late.

308
00:23:04,091 --> 00:23:05,592
It's almost time.

309
00:23:12,349 --> 00:23:15,811
Do you think it's reliable information?

310
00:23:19,523 --> 00:23:22,442
I proposed her a deal with the blueprint.

311
00:23:22,526 --> 00:23:25,028
Usually, people would say yes
even if they didn't mean it.

312
00:23:25,112 --> 00:23:26,404
There's nothing to lose.

313
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:28,240
She got an offer from the opposing party

314
00:23:28,323 --> 00:23:29,950
when the administration
is about to change.

315
00:23:31,868 --> 00:23:34,871
But Agent Han turn the offer down.

316
00:23:36,373 --> 00:23:37,541
I trust her.

317
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:44,506
AGENT HAN NA-GYEONG

318
00:23:46,883 --> 00:23:48,635
Please stay away.
There was an accident here.

319
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:53,932
-There's been an accident.
-Please step away.

320
00:23:54,224 --> 00:23:55,142
Excuse me.

321
00:23:56,726 --> 00:23:58,645
Ma'am. Ma'am.

322
00:23:59,479 --> 00:24:01,481
Have you heard from the informant yet?

323
00:24:02,232 --> 00:24:04,442
It's been an hour already.

324
00:24:04,734 --> 00:24:07,863
We need to finish it up by today, ma'am.

325
00:24:08,446 --> 00:24:12,492
She said he's unqualified for the position
of Minister of National Defense.

326
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:15,328
Security is important now more than ever.

327
00:24:15,412 --> 00:24:16,621
This is about...

328
00:24:18,248 --> 00:24:19,833
appointing Minister of National Defense.

329
00:24:20,959 --> 00:24:23,253
Please just trust me
and give it some more time.

330
00:24:23,336 --> 00:24:24,921
I trust you.

331
00:24:25,672 --> 00:24:27,883
But will the other members
trust you as well?

332
00:24:29,384 --> 00:24:32,804
You failed to scout Assemblyman Oh,

333
00:24:33,930 --> 00:24:36,266
and everyone in there knows that.

334
00:24:38,018 --> 00:24:40,729
You were against establishing
a nonparty cabinet too.

335
00:24:43,648 --> 00:24:46,610
If it gets any more delayed,

336
00:24:46,693 --> 00:24:48,528
they will say things

337
00:24:48,612 --> 00:24:51,865
like you're trying to ruin the hearing
and besmirch him out of personal reasons.

338
00:25:00,332 --> 00:25:02,500
Ma'am, can you hear me?

339
00:25:06,963 --> 00:25:07,964
Ma'am.

340
00:25:19,309 --> 00:25:21,770
Ma'am, please stay...

341
00:25:22,270 --> 00:25:23,563
where you are.

342
00:26:18,159 --> 00:26:19,619
You did great.

343
00:26:19,744 --> 00:26:20,870
Thank you.

344
00:26:20,954 --> 00:26:22,289
Congratulations.

345
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:23,707
Thank you.

346
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:24,833
I'll see you around.

347
00:26:24,916 --> 00:26:26,251
Congratulations, Assemblyman Oh.

348
00:26:29,504 --> 00:26:31,256
Your hard work didn't go unnoticed too.

349
00:26:32,716 --> 00:26:37,053
You managed to survive not only
on the battlefield but even a bombing.

350
00:26:38,555 --> 00:26:42,142
That kind of luck
never strikes a person even once,

351
00:26:42,225 --> 00:26:43,435
but it happened

352
00:26:44,561 --> 00:26:45,603
to you twice.

353
00:26:47,522 --> 00:26:48,606
Luck?

354
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:51,776
Do you believe
you'll always be this lucky?

355
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:56,698
At least for today, it seems like

356
00:26:57,615 --> 00:26:59,534
Lady Luck is on my side,

357
00:27:00,618 --> 00:27:01,828
not yours.

358
00:27:02,662 --> 00:27:03,830
I'll see you then.

359
00:27:11,171 --> 00:27:12,797
Assemblyman Oh's confirmation hearing

360
00:27:13,381 --> 00:27:15,091
just ended, sir.

361
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:20,096
His appointment was accepted
without any specific hitches.

362
00:27:20,180 --> 00:27:21,264
CERTIFICATE OF APPOINTMENT

363
00:27:28,438 --> 00:27:31,483
Is it too far into the night
to meet Assemblyman Oh?

364
00:27:32,067 --> 00:27:33,443
What is it about?

365
00:27:34,986 --> 00:27:37,989
He was here on that day.

366
00:27:38,073 --> 00:27:39,449
PERSONNEL FILE
JEONG HAN-MO

367
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:43,495
The day Agent Jeong came here
to debrief me on the interrogation.

368
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:46,206
Something about him felt off.

369
00:27:46,998 --> 00:27:47,874
Agent Jeong?

370
00:27:48,583 --> 00:27:49,542
Yes.

371
00:27:49,959 --> 00:27:53,254
He said he had a lead
on the Myung Hae-joon Case,

372
00:27:53,338 --> 00:27:54,631
but quickly changed his word.

373
00:27:55,090 --> 00:27:57,384
It's as if he had become
a different person.

374
00:28:02,722 --> 00:28:03,765
I want to know

375
00:28:04,808 --> 00:28:06,601
if Mr. Oh thinks the same way.

376
00:28:07,102 --> 00:28:08,937
What's there to be curious about?

377
00:28:09,437 --> 00:28:10,522
The answer is clear as day.

378
00:28:11,022 --> 00:28:13,733
A witness who holds
the key to the investigation

379
00:28:13,817 --> 00:28:16,528
suddenly changes his or her statement?

380
00:28:17,654 --> 00:28:21,366
That only happens when
someone who shouldn't hear it is present.

381
00:28:22,826 --> 00:28:24,202
Who was in the room with you?

382
00:28:26,121 --> 00:28:27,580
Do you have any leads?

383
00:28:27,664 --> 00:28:29,833
Yes, I believe so.

384
00:28:29,916 --> 00:28:31,084
This way.

385
00:28:31,835 --> 00:28:33,128
I'm glad to hear that.

386
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:43,680
It's a relief.

387
00:28:46,891 --> 00:28:49,394
I had no idea you'd be here too.

388
00:28:56,818 --> 00:28:58,862
CURRENT AFFAIRS CHANNEL

389
00:29:00,780 --> 00:29:05,702
HOW DID THE SURVIVOR OH YEONG-SEOK
BECOME THE NATION'S HERO?

390
00:29:18,214 --> 00:29:19,340
Yes, over here.

391
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:26,890
Make sure it's in line.

392
00:29:26,973 --> 00:29:28,266
Nice.

393
00:29:30,435 --> 00:29:32,854
-Ms. Kim.
-Yes?

394
00:29:33,938 --> 00:29:35,273
No one will give you a merit badge

395
00:29:35,356 --> 00:29:38,818
for saving duct tape in the Blue House.

396
00:29:38,902 --> 00:29:41,529
Don't you know that
this is President Park's first time

397
00:29:41,613 --> 00:29:42,989
at an event like this?

398
00:29:43,072 --> 00:29:44,783
Look where you marked, for example.

399
00:29:45,867 --> 00:29:49,120
All right. One, two, three.

400
00:29:49,204 --> 00:29:50,371
The spot...

401
00:29:51,122 --> 00:29:53,082
I see you marked the right spot.

402
00:30:01,132 --> 00:30:03,468
Secretary Cha, did you call for me?

403
00:30:03,551 --> 00:30:05,386
Gosh, look at the dust on your suit.

404
00:30:05,470 --> 00:30:06,596
And who are you again?

405
00:30:06,888 --> 00:30:08,223
-Sorry?
-Let me ask you all this.

406
00:30:08,973 --> 00:30:11,351
Raise your hand
if you heard me calling for him.

407
00:30:12,352 --> 00:30:13,478
No?

408
00:30:14,020 --> 00:30:16,189
Ms. Kim, you're doing a great job.

409
00:30:24,781 --> 00:30:26,658
CERTIFICATE OF APPOINTMENT
OH YEONG-SEOK

410
00:30:28,535 --> 00:30:29,619
ACTING PRESIDENT PARK MU-JIN

411
00:30:29,702 --> 00:30:31,246
CERTIFICATE OF APPOINTMENT
OH YEONG-SEOK

412
00:30:31,329 --> 00:30:34,541
Minister candidate Oh Yeong-seok's
approval rating has skyrocketed.

413
00:30:35,041 --> 00:30:37,585
With a rating of 19.8 percent,

414
00:30:37,669 --> 00:30:40,672
he's even ahead of Yun Chan-gyeong
in the presidential race.

415
00:30:41,172 --> 00:30:44,300
He's in second place
right behind President Park.

416
00:30:45,218 --> 00:30:46,177
He must've

417
00:30:47,095 --> 00:30:50,557
won over the public
at his hearing yesterday.

418
00:30:51,307 --> 00:30:54,769
His rating has been measured
ever since he gave his eulogy,

419
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:56,688
and it's been on the rise.

420
00:30:57,897 --> 00:30:59,274
It's quite funny if you ask me.

421
00:31:01,985 --> 00:31:05,488
The two with the highest approval ratings

422
00:31:05,572 --> 00:31:08,449
are both survivors of this recent attack.

423
00:31:08,533 --> 00:31:10,493
It reflects how much

424
00:31:10,577 --> 00:31:12,996
the people were terrorized by it.

425
00:31:13,746 --> 00:31:16,207
That fear had them
make heroes out of the survivors.

426
00:31:16,291 --> 00:31:20,086
It was one heck of a move
to have Mr. Oh join the nonparty cabinet.

427
00:31:20,545 --> 00:31:23,756
I'm sure it'll immensely help
President Park run the government.

428
00:31:24,799 --> 00:31:26,009
Good job.

429
00:31:36,686 --> 00:31:37,604
I had a tip

430
00:31:38,354 --> 00:31:41,149
that implied how Assemblyman Oh
is unfit to be a minister.

431
00:31:42,483 --> 00:31:46,112
The tip came from Agent Han Na-gyeong
of the NIS Terrorism Task Force.

432
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:48,948
Please have a seat.

433
00:31:56,497 --> 00:31:58,833
What disqualifies him of being appointed?

434
00:32:00,126 --> 00:32:01,252
What was the tip?

435
00:32:02,211 --> 00:32:03,504
I don't know yet.

436
00:32:04,714 --> 00:32:08,635
She called me on the road
and asked me to stall the hearing.

437
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:12,180
I haven't heard back from her
even up until this moment though.

438
00:32:14,432 --> 00:32:15,808
Around the same time,

439
00:32:16,142 --> 00:32:18,978
a big car accident occurred
near where the hearing was being held.

440
00:32:19,062 --> 00:32:20,480
Odd, right?

441
00:32:20,980 --> 00:32:23,775
However, no one with injuries
from a car crash

442
00:32:23,858 --> 00:32:26,569
was admitted to
any of the hospitals near the site.

443
00:32:26,653 --> 00:32:30,365
Do you think that
Agent Han was a victim of the accident?

444
00:32:30,448 --> 00:32:32,116
I don't think it was an accident.

445
00:32:34,243 --> 00:32:35,453
Agent Han told me

446
00:32:36,245 --> 00:32:39,874
that she had definitive proof regarding
the National Assembly Building bombing.

447
00:32:40,166 --> 00:32:44,128
She was even adamant about
Assemblyman Oh being unfit for Minister.

448
00:32:44,545 --> 00:32:48,633
But then she disappeared
without a single trace.

449
00:32:50,635 --> 00:32:53,346
Do you suspect Assemblyman Oh?

450
00:32:57,141 --> 00:32:58,226
And you're suspecting me.

451
00:32:58,810 --> 00:32:59,769
Mr. Oh

452
00:33:00,770 --> 00:33:02,855
has devoted his life to this country.

453
00:33:02,939 --> 00:33:06,734
And you think I'm crossing into
a dangerous territory by accusing him.

454
00:33:07,068 --> 00:33:09,153
I'm here without any proof after all.

455
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:12,657
You must think it's to put a dent
in your nonparty cabinet.

456
00:33:18,287 --> 00:33:21,165
I didn't actually think
you'd agree with me easily.

457
00:33:21,749 --> 00:33:22,583
Why not?

458
00:33:22,667 --> 00:33:25,962
You're probably scared
because I could be right.

459
00:33:27,505 --> 00:33:30,925
It would be even scarier to admit

460
00:33:31,009 --> 00:33:34,470
that you were wrong
in appointing him as Minister.

461
00:33:35,179 --> 00:33:36,014
Aren't I right?

462
00:33:48,651 --> 00:33:50,486
Please take care of this. Thanks.

463
00:33:58,870 --> 00:33:59,996
You're actually

464
00:34:00,455 --> 00:34:02,665
more competent that I gave you credit for.

465
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:06,711
President Park
has become a true politician.

466
00:34:21,309 --> 00:34:23,436
Secretary Cha, call the NIS.

467
00:34:23,519 --> 00:34:25,021
I need to verify something.

468
00:34:57,720 --> 00:35:00,223
I heard that Agent Han
found definitive proof regarding

469
00:35:00,473 --> 00:35:02,475
the National Assembly Building bombing.
Is this true?

470
00:35:02,558 --> 00:35:03,476
Sorry?

471
00:35:04,018 --> 00:35:06,104
What do you mean by definitive proof?

472
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:10,566
Oh, I must apologize, sir.

473
00:35:10,858 --> 00:35:14,570
Chief Jeong and Agent Han
were asked to debrief you in person,

474
00:35:14,654 --> 00:35:17,657
-so I am not aware of all the findings--
-Agent Han.

475
00:35:19,075 --> 00:35:19,992
Where is she right now?

476
00:35:21,744 --> 00:35:25,206
There's an issue with Agent Han
at the moment.

477
00:35:28,501 --> 00:35:31,045
The State Bureau of Investigation
informed her

478
00:35:31,337 --> 00:35:34,173
that they'd be looking into her
being Agent Jeong's accomplice.

479
00:35:34,257 --> 00:35:36,926
She must've gotten scared
because she's gone AWOL.

480
00:35:39,679 --> 00:35:41,097
The agency

481
00:35:41,389 --> 00:35:44,100
is doing its best
to locate her as we speak.

482
00:35:53,943 --> 00:35:56,487
Please report back to me
as soon as you find her.

483
00:35:57,405 --> 00:35:59,323
I need to ask her something in person.

484
00:36:04,579 --> 00:36:05,872
Yes, Mr. President.

485
00:36:56,923 --> 00:36:58,007
Hey, you're up.

486
00:37:07,683 --> 00:37:09,060
Drink this.

487
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:13,856
What happened?

488
00:37:16,108 --> 00:37:17,610
How did I get here?

489
00:37:18,945 --> 00:37:20,613
You took the words right out of my mouth.

490
00:37:21,822 --> 00:37:23,199
I received a call.

491
00:37:23,449 --> 00:37:25,826
They said you were in an accident
and asked me for my address.

492
00:37:27,245 --> 00:37:28,246
A call?

493
00:37:30,081 --> 00:37:31,249
From whom?

494
00:37:34,377 --> 00:37:36,504
Let's check the caller ID.

495
00:37:47,348 --> 00:37:48,975
What's the number?

496
00:37:52,228 --> 00:37:53,479
It was from a payphone

497
00:37:53,980 --> 00:37:55,898
somewhere near
the Seoul Metropolitan Council.

498
00:37:56,524 --> 00:37:57,900
A payphone?

499
00:37:58,276 --> 00:37:59,402
Who could've been?

500
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:02,113
The bell rang, so I opened the door.

501
00:38:02,196 --> 00:38:04,699
You were the only one outside.
Don't you remember?

502
00:38:23,801 --> 00:38:25,928
Do you remember who it was?

503
00:38:28,055 --> 00:38:28,931
No.

504
00:38:42,695 --> 00:38:44,488
MS. YUN CHAN-GYEONG

505
00:38:49,285 --> 00:38:50,536
Why aren't you answering?

506
00:38:50,619 --> 00:38:53,497
The only person who knew
I was headed to the hearing

507
00:38:53,873 --> 00:38:55,458
was Ms. Yun.

508
00:38:58,961 --> 00:39:01,172
So the car accident wasn't random.

509
00:39:06,385 --> 00:39:07,219
CALL HISTORY

510
00:39:07,303 --> 00:39:10,097
POWER OFF

511
00:39:13,642 --> 00:39:15,478
Ji-won, we can only

512
00:39:16,145 --> 00:39:17,938
trust each other right now.

513
00:39:27,740 --> 00:39:28,741
What about the hearing?

514
00:39:29,950 --> 00:39:32,161
Was Assemblyman Oh's appointment approved?

515
00:39:36,582 --> 00:39:38,000
Congratulations.

516
00:39:40,127 --> 00:39:41,796
I heard that

517
00:39:41,879 --> 00:39:44,340
your appointment was approved
with a unanimous vote.

518
00:39:45,299 --> 00:39:46,342
Thank you.

519
00:39:48,803 --> 00:39:51,972
I'm guessing you didn't
hear the news though.

520
00:39:53,516 --> 00:39:56,644
The head of the congressional hearing
informed me

521
00:39:57,728 --> 00:40:00,731
that Agent Han of the NIS
tipped Ms. Yun off

522
00:40:01,774 --> 00:40:04,068
about there being
a reason for disqualification.

523
00:40:07,822 --> 00:40:10,074
Although, it turned out to be nothing.

524
00:40:13,828 --> 00:40:16,414
Why do you think Agent Han said so though?

525
00:40:17,748 --> 00:40:21,043
