while I lived.

533
00:40:46,152 --> 00:40:48,279
She's been suspicious of my survival

534
00:40:48,362 --> 00:40:49,780
from the get-go.

535
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:56,120
No matter how many times it's explained,

536
00:40:57,496 --> 00:40:59,290
even though it's the truth,

537
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:02,001
it'll be hard for her to accept.

538
00:41:04,587 --> 00:41:05,838
I've been there myself.

539
00:41:09,133 --> 00:41:10,926
After the Battle of Baengnyeong?

540
00:41:13,888 --> 00:41:15,347
Living in South Korea

541
00:41:16,432 --> 00:41:17,975
only ends in two ways.

542
00:41:19,351 --> 00:41:21,145
You either become a victim one day

543
00:41:23,314 --> 00:41:24,857
or the bereaved.

544
00:41:27,776 --> 00:41:29,612
That day at sea,

545
00:41:31,197 --> 00:41:34,408
I asked myself over and over again

546
00:41:35,576 --> 00:41:37,203
why those innocent young souls had to die.

547
00:41:39,038 --> 00:41:40,539
I just couldn't accept the truth.

548
00:41:42,958 --> 00:41:44,460
I couldn't believe it.

549
00:41:48,214 --> 00:41:49,381
However,

550
00:41:50,424 --> 00:41:52,551
nobody gave me an answer.

551
00:41:55,346 --> 00:41:57,681
The conservatives
who uses national security to score votes

552
00:41:59,683 --> 00:42:01,101
took advantage of us,

553
00:42:02,603 --> 00:42:04,563
and the progressives
who cry peace for their votes

554
00:42:06,273 --> 00:42:07,983
turned a blind eye.

555
00:42:11,153 --> 00:42:12,029
Is that why

556
00:42:13,113 --> 00:42:14,990
you got into politics?

557
00:42:17,451 --> 00:42:19,745
I chose a path
where I could find the answers myself.

558
00:42:23,082 --> 00:42:24,333
And Agent Han

559
00:42:25,626 --> 00:42:27,211
is one of the people

560
00:42:28,087 --> 00:42:29,588
that I wish

561
00:42:30,965 --> 00:42:31,924
to speak for.

562
00:42:53,404 --> 00:42:55,531
What time is the investiture
for the new ministers?

563
00:42:55,614 --> 00:42:57,241
It's at 2 p.m., ma'am.

564
00:42:57,908 --> 00:43:01,745
Will President Park appoint
Assemblyman Oh as a minister?

565
00:43:02,329 --> 00:43:03,247
I don't know,

566
00:43:03,539 --> 00:43:05,332
but it feels like I'm being evaluated.

567
00:43:05,416 --> 00:43:06,542
Excuse me?

568
00:43:06,625 --> 00:43:09,044
If he trusts me as a politician,

569
00:43:09,295 --> 00:43:10,754
he'll reconsider.

570
00:43:11,463 --> 00:43:13,632
If he appoints Assemblyman Oh,

571
00:43:14,508 --> 00:43:16,677
won't that mean he doesn't trust me?

572
00:43:18,345 --> 00:43:19,555
I wonder

573
00:43:19,972 --> 00:43:22,558
what kind of choice
President Park will make.

574
00:43:42,202 --> 00:43:44,413
I've chosen to answer myself.

575
00:43:56,008 --> 00:43:58,761
It's time to leave, sir.

576
00:43:58,844 --> 00:44:00,638
The investiture will start soon.

577
00:44:05,309 --> 00:44:06,185
Okay.

578
00:45:45,784 --> 00:45:47,786
You'd like to postpone the investiture?

579
