and say it was bad government.

599
00:46:47,387 --> 00:46:50,474
You're the biggest threat
to Assemblywoman Yun

600
00:46:50,557 --> 00:46:52,100
as a presidential candidate.

601
00:46:54,728 --> 00:46:56,605
Other than Assemblywoman Yun's claim,

602
00:46:56,980 --> 00:46:58,357
we currently have no evidence

603
00:46:58,690 --> 00:47:01,401
on the suspicions of Assemblyman Oh, sir.

604
00:47:02,277 --> 00:47:03,362
Assemblywoman Yun

605
00:47:03,445 --> 00:47:06,365
was trying to get you impeached
just a few days ago.

606
00:47:06,865 --> 00:47:08,575
She's a master in politics.

607
00:47:08,742 --> 00:47:10,702
She may have other intentions, sir.

608
00:47:10,786 --> 00:47:11,787
What should I do?

609
00:47:11,870 --> 00:47:13,705
Should I call the ceremony hall?

610
00:47:13,789 --> 00:47:15,499
It isn't too late yet.

611
00:47:24,341 --> 00:47:25,634
Let me ask you one thing.

612
00:47:26,969 --> 00:47:27,970
Isn't the hearing

613
00:47:28,554 --> 00:47:30,222
a verification process

614
00:47:30,597 --> 00:47:32,099
of candidates by the National Assembly?

615
00:47:36,270 --> 00:47:37,521
The opposing party

616
00:47:37,938 --> 00:47:39,147
asked for a verification,

617
00:47:39,231 --> 00:47:41,608
and I just faithfully complied to it.

618
00:47:43,318 --> 00:47:44,903
Have I created a controversy

619
00:47:45,654 --> 00:47:47,990
that you have to object to?

620
00:48:08,635 --> 00:48:09,886
Then

621
00:48:10,429 --> 00:48:11,805
when you met with Assemblyman Oh,

622
00:48:11,888 --> 00:48:14,683
did you find him suspicious in any way?

623
00:48:15,142 --> 00:48:16,059
It's the opposite.

624
00:48:16,143 --> 00:48:18,437
Then why are you taking such a big chance?

625
00:48:18,520 --> 00:48:21,648
Don't you see
what Assemblywoman Yun wants?

626
00:48:21,732 --> 00:48:23,650
Assemblyman Oh is someone everyone--

627
00:48:23,734 --> 00:48:25,527
I don't know what Assemblywoman Yun wants

628
00:48:25,986 --> 00:48:27,988
or what kind of person Assemblyman Oh is.

629
00:48:28,947 --> 00:48:32,242
I want to trust them, but can't.
As for now, I don't even know

630
00:48:32,326 --> 00:48:33,994
whether they are friend or foe.

631
00:48:36,246 --> 00:48:38,040
So I've decided to choose neither of them.

632
00:48:38,123 --> 00:48:40,250
-Mr. President.
-What I believe in...

633
00:48:41,501 --> 00:48:44,087
are the principles and system
of our administration.

634
00:48:46,173 --> 00:48:48,008
It's controlled our nation so far.

635
00:48:51,553 --> 00:48:54,514
Until Assemblyman Oh is verified,

636
00:48:57,059 --> 00:48:59,227
I don't plan to appoint him
Minister of National Defense.

637
00:49:01,063 --> 00:49:02,439
The nonparty cabinet

638
00:49:03,899 --> 00:49:07,611
was a test to verify
your administrative ability.

639
00:49:09,196 --> 00:49:10,697
If you postpone the investiture

640
00:49:11,281 --> 00:49:13,283
and withdraw his nomination,

641
00:49:14,576 --> 00:49:17,913
that will clearly become

642
00:49:18,497 --> 00:49:21,416
your error and misadministration.

643
00:49:21,500 --> 00:49:24,127
Your approval rating
will definitely plunge.

644
00:49:24,211 --> 00:49:25,712
Are you okay with that?

645
00:49:26,546 --> 00:49:28,215
You want me to be
a presidential candidate?

646
00:49:28,298 --> 00:49:29,508
Yes.

647
00:49:32,928 --> 00:49:36,556
I can't be the candidate that has
a good chance of winning

648
00:49:37,849 --> 00:49:39,601
like you want me to be.

649
00:49:43,772 --> 00:49:44,690
That's my answer.

650
00:49:51,905 --> 00:49:52,989
Yes, sir.

651
00:50:02,708 --> 00:50:04,167
I'll have the investiture...

652
00:50:06,128 --> 00:50:09,256
postponed as you wish, sir.

653
00:50:35,991 --> 00:50:37,659
What did he say?

654
00:50:39,161 --> 00:50:41,496
He just isn't used to this.

655
00:50:41,872 --> 00:50:44,249
Taking chances on political matters

656
00:50:44,666 --> 00:50:45,792
or how the Blue House works.

657
00:50:49,463 --> 00:50:51,006
He isn't used to it?

658
00:50:52,674 --> 00:50:55,343
The President isn't desperate enough.

659
00:50:56,678 --> 00:50:57,596
I

660
00:50:58,263 --> 00:50:59,598
think every day

661
00:50:59,681 --> 00:51:02,267
that during the previous government,
we should've used the power

662
00:51:02,350 --> 00:51:04,060
we had to fight and win

663
00:51:04,144 --> 00:51:06,480
against the opposing party
or anyone that were against us

664
00:51:06,563 --> 00:51:07,731
by any means.

665
00:51:09,065 --> 00:51:10,776
If we didn't give them an excuse

666
00:51:10,859 --> 00:51:13,069
or even the smallest reason to attack us,

667
00:51:13,153 --> 00:51:17,115
if we pushed back harder,
if I just insisted to the President...

668
00:51:20,452 --> 00:51:21,661
more strongly...

669
00:51:26,625 --> 00:51:27,626
Then...

670
00:51:29,252 --> 00:51:30,504
he wouldn't...

671
00:51:31,671 --> 00:51:32,798
have been ridiculed...

672
00:51:34,382 --> 00:51:36,802
throughout his entire term,

673
00:51:38,637 --> 00:51:39,638
nor...

674
00:51:41,890 --> 00:51:44,935
would he have gone down in history
so pathetically.

675
00:51:53,693 --> 00:51:55,278
President Yang Jin-man...

676
00:51:58,824 --> 00:52:02,160
was the kindest person I've ever met.

677
00:52:19,177 --> 00:52:21,096
That's why we failed.

678
00:52:39,364 --> 00:52:40,866
I really don't understand.

679
00:52:41,283 --> 00:52:43,994
Why did Han-mo confess
that he killed Myung Hae-joon?

680
00:52:46,288 --> 00:52:48,707
I need to ask around

681
00:52:48,874 --> 00:52:50,625
to find out what happened to Han-mo.

682
00:52:52,127 --> 00:52:55,005
You can't be careless like that.
Don't you get it?

683
00:52:55,630 --> 00:52:57,591
We've all fallen into a trap.

684
00:52:58,925 --> 00:53:00,176
Han-mo went to the Blue House

685
00:53:00,260 --> 00:53:02,345
to report Assemblyman Oh
to higher authorities

686
00:53:02,429 --> 00:53:04,139
and got locked up as a murderer.

687
00:53:04,723 --> 00:53:07,684
You almost died
on your way to the hearing.

688
00:53:08,393 --> 00:53:09,895
I followed your orders,

689
00:53:10,729 --> 00:53:12,063
and now I've been suspended

690
00:53:12,731 --> 00:53:14,524
indefinitely without pay.

691
00:53:17,736 --> 00:53:19,905
I haven't even paid off my car yet.

692
00:53:23,408 --> 00:53:25,035
Are you trying to make me feel bad?

693
00:53:25,118 --> 00:53:26,369
No, I'm not.

694
00:53:27,412 --> 00:53:29,956
I'm saying an agent's commitment
isn't a virtue,

695
00:53:30,540 --> 00:53:31,708
but an obligation.

696
00:53:33,376 --> 00:53:34,920
It's what you said.

697
00:53:37,088 --> 00:53:40,508
Something this cliche should be
engraved in stone for the NIS.

698
00:53:41,718 --> 00:53:43,303
Who in the world said that to you?

699
00:53:45,722 --> 00:53:47,057
The agent who trained me.

700
00:53:48,141 --> 00:53:49,768
Kim Jun-o of Espionage Team Two.

701
00:54:06,576 --> 00:54:08,328
This is Myung Hae-joon's killer.

702
00:54:11,539 --> 00:54:14,542
Is he the one that attacked you yesterday?

703
00:54:19,798 --> 00:54:21,633
It's him.

704
00:54:23,510 --> 00:54:24,427
Tae-ik.

705
00:54:56,126 --> 00:54:56,960
Do you work out?

706
00:54:58,378 --> 00:54:59,671
You've lost weight.

707
00:55:00,255 --> 00:55:01,923
Golf isn't much exercise.

708
00:55:03,967 --> 00:55:05,969
I can't seem to lower my score.

709
00:55:08,471 --> 00:55:10,515
It's always above 80.

710
00:55:17,188 --> 00:55:20,191
Maybe I lost weight
because I have much to worry about.

711
00:55:22,402 --> 00:55:24,279
Two of my men...

712
00:55:26,406 --> 00:55:29,242
I'm really sad, Mr. Kim.

713
00:55:29,826 --> 00:55:31,369
Make sure I don't have to worry.

714
00:55:33,788 --> 00:55:37,709
I told my men in the State Bureau
of Investigation to find Na-gyeong.

715
00:55:40,086 --> 00:55:42,630
The Blue House wasn't doing anything.

716
00:55:43,131 --> 00:55:46,176
Would you like cuffs this time?

717
00:55:46,259 --> 00:55:48,219
You have to find her first.

718
00:55:49,387 --> 00:55:51,306
Don't have others do it,
but find her yourself.

719
00:55:55,977 --> 00:55:58,980
Outsourcing causes problems.
Isn't that right, Mr. Kim?

720
00:55:59,064 --> 00:56:02,442
You need to learn how to wait
after giving orders

721
00:56:02,525 --> 00:56:03,735
for your men to grow.

722
00:56:05,779 --> 00:56:08,406
Is that how the VIP taught you?

723
00:56:10,241 --> 00:56:12,243
He trusts you too much.

724
00:56:16,247 --> 00:56:19,250
Those that are in charge
of state affairs don't even meet.

725
00:56:19,334 --> 00:56:21,086
We don't know each other's names or faces.

726
00:56:22,170 --> 00:56:24,714
How will we get anything done
without being connected?

727
00:56:24,798 --> 00:56:26,800
Isn't it better not to know...

728
00:56:27,842 --> 00:56:28,885
for everyone?

729
00:57:03,920 --> 00:57:05,046
Did I keep you waiting?

730
00:57:09,092 --> 00:57:11,511
They must get chatty with age.

731
00:57:11,886 --> 00:57:13,221
Director Ji...

732
00:57:15,140 --> 00:57:17,725
seemed to be hoping you'd meet with him.

733
00:57:19,477 --> 00:57:21,729
He works in the shadows
but wants to stand in the light?

734
00:57:22,063 --> 00:57:23,398
Silent commitment.

735
00:57:24,357 --> 00:57:27,235
I wonder why people engrave
that on stone...

736
00:57:28,278 --> 00:57:29,612
when they can't live up to it.

737
00:57:30,864 --> 00:57:34,534
President Park seems to be looking
for Agent Han.

738
00:57:36,244 --> 00:57:38,496
Director Ji will take care of her,
so the investiture

739
00:57:38,580 --> 00:57:40,832
for the Minister of National Defense
goes smoothly.

740
00:57:42,333 --> 00:57:44,085
Is the investiture that important?

741
00:57:45,879 --> 00:57:47,964
I think we got everything we needed

742
00:57:48,840 --> 00:57:49,966
during the hearing.

743
00:57:52,677 --> 00:57:53,803
I saw

744
00:57:54,888 --> 00:57:58,433
that your approval rating soared
after the hearing,

745
00:58:00,059 --> 00:58:02,729
and you are up there with President Park.

746
00:58:04,731 --> 00:58:07,275
Now, everyone will move
with the presidential election in mind,

747
00:58:07,358 --> 00:58:10,153
including Assemblywoman Yun
and the Blue House.

748
00:58:10,778 --> 00:58:11,863
Those people...

749
00:58:13,740 --> 00:58:15,658
How great a world
are they trying to create?

750
00:58:17,785 --> 00:58:20,079
If we could change the world
with an election,

751
00:58:22,081 --> 00:58:23,416
humans...

752
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:26,586
would have done everything
to get rid of elections.

753
00:58:28,671 --> 00:58:30,048
And a long time ago at that.

754
00:58:35,803 --> 00:58:36,888
Don't you agree?

755
00:58:37,472 --> 00:58:41,017
That's why elections are like
Santa Claus to adults.

756
00:58:42,060 --> 00:58:44,229
It's a lie we want to believe in.

757
00:58:47,649 --> 00:58:51,819
Don't you think you can give people
their gift?

758
00:58:53,821 --> 00:58:56,366
President Park won't be registered...

759
00:58:57,659 --> 00:58:58,743
as a presidential candidate.

760
00:59:10,129 --> 00:59:13,299
What should we tell the press
about the postponement?

761
00:59:18,846 --> 00:59:21,099
Let's say it's a problem
in administrative procedure.

762
00:59:21,933 --> 00:59:24,102
It's a first with an acting president.

763
00:59:24,936 --> 00:59:25,979
Whom do you have in mind?

764
00:59:28,189 --> 00:59:30,441
The presidential candidate registration
is in 10 days.

765
00:59:31,401 --> 00:59:33,194
President Park turned you down.

766
00:59:36,573 --> 00:59:39,075
But...

767
00:59:39,659 --> 00:59:42,579
I'm sure someone new

768
00:59:42,662 --> 00:59:45,415
will show up
as the presidential candidate.

769
00:59:50,169 --> 00:59:51,462
Good luck!

770
00:59:57,760 --> 01:00:01,389
Nothing in this house is off the record
nor do embargoes work.

771
01:00:03,057 --> 01:00:04,767
-Is this true?
-Please answer us!

772
01:00:12,859 --> 01:00:14,152
What is it?

773
01:00:20,533 --> 01:00:21,868
Who could it have been?

774
01:00:23,286 --> 01:00:24,662
Why bother now?

775
01:00:25,163 --> 01:00:27,415
It's a scandal
regarding Yang Jin-man's ministers.

776
01:00:27,832 --> 01:00:31,002
Why would they release a scandal
about those who are already dead?

777
01:00:32,128 --> 01:00:33,921
Why do you think they tipped off
the press?

778
01:00:34,672 --> 01:00:35,798
How is the press responding?

779
01:00:35,882 --> 01:00:39,093
So you're saying that the same tip
was given to Joongang Daily,

780
01:00:39,177 --> 01:00:41,137
the public TV, and the news channel,
right?

781
01:00:44,891 --> 01:00:48,061
That's an internal document
with the Blue House's mark on it.

782
01:00:49,354 --> 01:00:51,689
Was there a whistle-blower? Who was it?

783
01:00:53,691 --> 01:00:54,776
Do you have no clue either?

784
01:00:54,859 --> 01:00:58,029
Even Jang-hyun, the chief
of the Blue House, had no idea either.

785
01:00:58,404 --> 01:00:59,614
Based on the tip,

786
01:01:00,365 --> 01:01:02,033
I'm certain it was a whistle-blower.

787
01:01:05,912 --> 01:01:07,580
The tip is...

788
01:01:07,664 --> 01:01:09,165
JANG GUN-HO'S
INVOLVEMENT IN CORRUPTION

789
01:01:10,416 --> 01:01:11,959
I can't believe them.

790
01:01:14,587 --> 01:01:17,006
"Jang Gun-ho, Former Minister
of National Defense's Involvement

791
01:01:17,090 --> 01:01:18,341
in Corruption.

